# ## How to maintain this .gitignore
# 
# 1. Explicitly declare what (patterns) we want to track; otherwise ignore everything else.
# 2. Breakup Filter Rules by Section; Each section must start with INCLUDE or EXCLUDE followed by a description of what/how you want to filter (separated by a colon)
# 3. Write the appropriate Filter; it's better to be prescriptive than vague.
# 4. Generally, Ignore everything & only track what you need.
# 
# ## How to Debug
# 
# Run the following & inspect the output
# 
# ```
# find . -path ./.git -prune -o -type f -print | sort | git check-ignore -v --stdin
# ```
# 
# ## How `.gitignore` Works
# 
# GitIgnore processes patterns sequentially from top to bottom.
# Later patterns override earlier ones. The '!' prefix negates a pattern, re-including previously excluded files.
# Patterns are relative to the .gitignore file location.

# EXCLUDE: Everything Everywhere by default
*

# INCLUDE: Directory Structure Preservation
!**/.gitkeep

# INCLUDE: Document Folder & MkDocs supported files
!docs/
!docs/**/
!docs/**/*.md
!docs/**/*.rst
!docs/**/*.txt
!docs/**/*.yml
!docs/**/*.yaml
!docs/**/*.png
!docs/**/*.jpg
!docs/**/*.svg

# INCLUDE: Helpers Folder & Contained Python Source Files, Scripts & Documents
!helpers/
!helpers/**/
!helpers/**/*.md
!helpers/**/*.py
!helpers/**/*.sh
!helpers/tool

# INCLUDE: Meta Folder & contained markdown documents
!meta/
!meta/**/
!meta/**/*.md
!meta/**/*.txt
!meta/**/*.yml
!meta/**/*.yaml

# INCLUDE: Models Folder & all Specifications & Documents
!models/
!models/**/
!models/**/*.md
!models/**/*.spec


# INCLUDE: Source Folder & contained Python Source Files & any Documentation
!src/
!src/**/
!src/**/*.md
!src/**/*.py
!src/**/*.pyi
!src/**/py.typed

# INCLUDE: Test Folder & contained Python Source Files
!tests/
!tests/**/
!tests/**/*.py

# INCLUDE: Vendor Folder & External Dependencies
!vendor/
!vendor/**

# INCLUDE: Project Root Files; NOTE: This is highly prescriptive; we don't want to clutter our Project Root
# Project Information
!README.md
!LICENSE
!CHANGELOG.md
!AGENT.md
!CONTRIBUTOR.md
# Python & Documentation Related Files
!.python-version
!pyproject.toml
!uv.lock
!mkdocs.yml
# NOTE: Version Control & Development Configuration Files
!.gitignore
!.gitmodules
!.gitattributes
!.pre-commit-config.yaml
!.envrc
